Home
This will describe the website and introduce that there will be a set of exercises, covering all muscles groups. A brief summary of what has been learned in the course will be included.

Code Editor
This section will describe and explain how a code editor is being used, based on Week 1. The how it has helped in developing assignments, web pages etc. Will be mentioned.

HTML
This page will introduce semantic structure of HTML, based on Week 2. It will explain how the webpages have been developed and constructed.

CSS
This page will explain elements learned during Weeks 3-5 and 10 concerning the presentation, layout (flexbox/grid) and styling of the websites, making it "good looking".

Accessibility
This page will describe elements concerning accessibility, based on Week 7 and Project 3. How the website should be made more accessible to the wide masses will be briefly discussed.

Ethics
This page will be about using media and content responsible in connection with what was discussed in Week 6 concerning ethical web-development. The use of images and suchlike will be considered.

Validation
This page will explain and describe the usage of validation services for HTML and CSS-code which was presented during later projects. It will emphasize the benefit of writing error-free code.

AI
This page will briefly mention how generative AI has been useful during the final project. It can also contain useful links or tips.

